==Japanese==
===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=irr}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (''c.'' 759 {{CE}}).

Various theories exist regarding the ultimate derivation:
* Possibly originally a compound of {{m|ja|明け|tr=ake}} + {{m|ja|時|tr=shida||[[hour]]}}
*: {{IPAfont|*⟨ake<sub>2</sub> sida⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/akəʲsida/}} → {{IPAchar|/asita/}} → {{IPAchar|/aɕita/}}
* Possibly cognate with {{m|ja|朝|tr=asa||[[morning]]}}, also read as ''ashita'', likely the original meaning and spelling

The kanji spelling is {{juku|sort=あした}}, from {{bor|ja|zh|sort=あした|-}} {{zh-l|明日}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{ja-l|朝}}

