===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=irr}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=あす|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (712 {{CE}}).

Various theories exist regarding the ultimate derivation:
* Possibly a shift from {{m|ja|明かす|tr=akasu||to [[pass]]}}
*: {{IPAfont|*/akasu/}} → *{{IPAchar|/akusu/}} → {{IPAchar|/asu/}}
* Possibly an apophonic form of or cognate with {{m|ja|朝|tr=asa||[[morning]]}}

The kanji spelling is {{juku}}, from {{bor|ja|zh|-}} {{zh-l|明日}}.

